.TH RCJPEG "1" "October 2018" "dotfiles" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
rcjpeg \- rcjpeg
.SH DESCRIPTION
Compress images using MozJpeg.
.PP
Allows compressing list of images files of various image formats using
ImageMagick and MozJpeg. Processed files are saved to the target directory,
mirroring the original relative directory layout as seen from the current
working directory.
.SS "Usage:"
.IP
$ rcjpeg [options] <filename ...>
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Print this message
.TP
\fB\-v\fR, \fB\-\-version\fR
Print version number
.TP
\fB\-D\fR, \fB\-\-dry\-run\fR
Dry\-run without writing
.TP
\fB\-F\fR, \fB\-\-force\fR
Allow overwriting existing files
.TP
\fB\-S\fR, \fB\-\-silent\fR
Silent mode
.TP
\fB\-V\fR, \fB\-\-verbose\fR
Verbose mode
.TP
\fB\-\-color\fR
Enable colors
.TP
\fB\-\-no\-color\fR
Disable colors
.HP
\fB\-d\fR <path>, \fB\-\-directory\fR[=\fI\,\/\fR]<path>
.IP
Directory to write processed files, defaults to 'compressed'
.HP
\fB\-e\fR <.ext>, \fB\-\-extension\fR[=\fI\,\/\fR]<.ext>
.IP
Output extension, defaults to '.jpg'
.HP
\fB\-o\fR <path>, \fB\-\-out\fR[=\fI\,\/\fR]<path>, \fB\-\-outfile\fR[=\fI\,\/\fR]<path>
.IP
Output file to write the processed data. If ends to a slash, is treated
as a directory, overriding  \fB\-\-directory\fR
.HP
\fB\-q\fR <integer>, \fB\-\-quality\fR[=\fI\,\/\fR]<integer>
.IP
Compression quality 0 \- 100, defaults to '80'
.SH EXAMPLES
.IP
\f(CW$ rcjpeg *.jpg\fR
.br
\f(CW$ rcjpeg < file.png > output.jpg\fR
.br
\f(CW$ rcjpeg -d path/to/output/directory -q 90 *.jpg\fR
